        <num>CC 962</num>
        <heading>962.  Presumption of acceptance</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 962.  Presumption of acceptance
In the absence of a renunciation, a successor is presumed to accept succession rights.  Nonetheless, for good cause the successor may be compelled to accept or renounce.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111092</p>
